node.text:
The Sector 9 Downhill Division loaded up the van in San Diego to make their way to Colorado for the Devil's Peak Downhill Race. Here's a taste of the action as they rolled through the states in search of their next adventure. Stay tuned as part 1 is dropping December 12th!

Riders: @ayyy_cole, @thebossducky, @micah.green, @oscargutierrez_stm, @aj_haiby, @louispilloni, @jimmyriha

Film/Edit @b_carolin_

#devilsgambletour

node.text:
Staring out the porthole, dreaming of the serene marine landscape? Envisioning perfect cerulean barrels? Well, we can't help you get there, but we can keep the fantasy going with the Mariner Maple Lookout. The Lookout in Bamboo construction is our best-selling board, so we duplicated the exact size and shape here, in Maple, for a different riding option. Whether you're pushing around town or just coasting down the boardwalk, all of our components work in unison with this iconic shape to provide you with a ride you'll never forget.

https://www.sector9.com/products/mariner-maple-lookout

Rider: @louispilloni 
Film: @coledownhill / @jimmyriha

node.title: 2019 MARINER MAPLE LOOKOUT - FEATURING LOUIS PILLONI

node.text:
Sector 9 has decided to partner on a new artistic collaboration in the Bamboo Series with French artist, The Minimalist Wave. Following a ritual process, he obsesses over the patterns of a wave crossing the planet, as it evolves constantly with new journeys and intersections. The pen and ink drawings are an invitation to find yourself in the heart of the ocean, to get lost and to discover imaginary worlds. The simple, minimalist illustrations provide a stark contrast to the Bamboo, creating beautiful decks worthy of hanging in a gallery just as much as they are riding to the beach.

RIDERS: NATHAN STROM AND REEF PERSIDOK

node.text: Is there anything better than just cruising? Cruising the halls at school, cruising down the boardwalk, or just cruising through life. These all evoke that relaxed feeling we crave, each and every day. We’ve been making Cruiser skateboards for years, and they have consistently helped us (and MANY others) unwind and let loose. Whether you’re in the mood to just glide or "smash, smother, and cut," our Cruiser Series boards are built to handle whatever you throw at them. Now all that's left to do is make your pick: Rock, Paper, or Scissors?

node.text: We are proud to introduce the new Feather Tia Pro, the Signature model for professional surfer and Sector 9 team rider Tia Blanco. Tia took her time in order to ensure the final product not only reflected her tastes, but also ended up being a highly functional skateboard. Small, easy-to-ride, lightweight and comfortable to travel with, the Feather Tia Pro is great choice for skaters of all abilities. Tia dreams of perfect waves, and we helped bring that idea to life in her new dream catcher graphic. To finish it off, we included her signature color scheme on the duotone bottom veneer.

node.text:
Are you afraid of the dark? Fear no more! The new Lumiskate Series (#s9lumiskate) allows you to take back the night! The #s9Phoenix and #s9Basilisk feature legendary Glow in the Dark graphics from artist, Daniel Sheridan. Double that up with the LED powered cores that charge the Glow in the Dark Lumithane wheels (#s9lumithane) to set your ride ablaze. They're perfect lighting up any skate outing, day or night.

PHOENIX - The most adaptable board in our Lumiskate Series, the Phoenix soars in the street, through the skatepark, and over any terrain you want to take it! 
BASILISK - A direct, shorter descendent of our OG Pin, the easy-to-ride Basilisk is ready lay down some classic lines. Snake your way down the boardwalk night or day.

node.text:
If the easy-to-ride boards in the Classix Series make you want to drop everything you’re doing and travel to a beautiful place (with your skateboard of course), then we’ve done our job. Scenic graphics, combined with classic (see, we DO know how to spell), timeless shapes, continue to be the foundation of what we do at Sector 9. These boards have stood the test of time and continue to roll mile after mile, all over the world.

Rider: Jimmy Riha

node.text: Wanna stop wiggling and put more power into your carves? If the answer is ‘Yes’, then these are the boards for you. The beauty of the Sidewinder Series comes straight from the trucks, which were specifically designed for carving. The extra kingpin and pivot engineered into the trucks give them something akin to that additional joint your fingers have, and provide you with a quick, responsive turning radius, that’s unlike anything you’ve ridden before.
